<subSubSection id="C3786552C653FFA3BA8FFA05B337F94A" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDD36D9C653FFA3BA8FFA05B062FA0C" blockId="12.[227,348,1493,1519]" box="[227,348,1493,1519]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<heading id="D09581B5C653FFA3BA8FFA05B062FA0C" bold="true" box="[227,348,1493,1519]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC653FFA3BA8FFA05B062FA0C" bold="true" box="[227,348,1493,1519]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDD36D9C653FFA3BA8FF9D4B337F94A" blockId="12.[226,1436,1540,1706]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC653FFA3BA8FF9D4B045F9FD" authorityName="Chamberlin" authorityYear="1919" box="[227,379,1540,1566]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="12" pageNumber="59" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pelogeniinae">Pelogeniinae</taxonomicName>
with prostomium oval, wider than long. Upper lip without facial tubercle. Median antennal ceratophore bulbous, base with ctenidia. Segment II with middorsal subtriangular lobe; neuropodia without appendages; neurochaetal blades bifid. Segment III without dorsal cirri; neuropodia with large, expanded balloon-like lobes on distal margin; neuropodial blades falcate, bifid or entire. First pair of elytra short or elongated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3786552C653FFA2BA8FF901B094FE6C" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDD36D9C653FFA3BA8FF901B06BF908" blockId="12.[227,341,1745,1771]" box="[227,341,1745,1771]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<heading id="D09581B5C653FFA3BA8FF901B06BF908" bold="true" box="[227,341,1745,1771]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC653FFA3BA8FF901B06BF908" bold="true" box="[227,341,1745,1771]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDD36D9C653FFA3BA8FF92FB4A2F7ED" blockId="12.[223,1437,1791,2063]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C653FFA3BA8FF92FB095F8FA" author="Pettibone M. H." box="[227,427,1791,1817]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 89" refId="ref30430" refString="Pettibone M. H. 1997. Revision of the sigalionid species (Polychaeta) referred to Psammolyce Kinberg, 1856, Pelogenia Schmarda, 1861, and belonging to the subfamily Pelogeniinae Chamberlin, 1919. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 581: 1 - 89. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.581" type="journal article" year="1997">Pettibone (1997)</bibRefCitation>
proposed 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC653FFA3B840F92FB211F8FA" authorityName="Pettibone" authorityYear="1997" box="[556,815,1791,1817]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Hartmanipsammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC653FFA3B840F92FB211F8FA" box="[556,815,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Hartmanipsammolyce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC653FFA3B916F8D0B53EF8FA" authorityName="Hartman" authorityYear="1942" box="[890,1024,1791,1817]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Psammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pendula">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC653FFA3B916F8D0B53EF8FA" box="[890,1024,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. pendula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<typeStatus id="54D9887BC653FFA3BE42F8D0B55FF8F9" box="[1070,1121,1792,1818]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">type</typeStatus>
species, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC653FFA3BF64F92FB33DF8DE" authority="Hartman, 1965" authorityName="Hartman" authorityYear="1965" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Psammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="globula">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC653FFA3BF64F92FB003F8DF" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Psammolyce globula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C653FFA3BB27F8F3B33DF8DE" author="Hartman O." box="[331,515,1826,1853]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref29666" refString="Hartman O. 1965. Deep-water Benthic Polychaetous Annelids off New England to Bermuda and Other North Atlantic Areas. Allan Hancock Foundation Publications, Occasional Paper 28." type="journal volume" year="1965">Hartman, 1965</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as its junior synonym. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C653FFA3B950F8F3B57DF8DF" author="Hartman O." box="[828,1091,1826,1853]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="89 - 104" refId="ref29558" refString="Hartman O. 1942 b. The polychaetous Annelida. In: Report on the Scientific results of the Atlantis expeditions to the West Indies under the Joint Auspices of the University of Havana and Harvard University. Memorias de la Sociedad Cubana de Historia Natural 16 (2): 89 - 104." type="journal article" year="1942">Hartman (1942b: 91)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC653FFA3BEBDF8F3B46BF8DF" authorityName="Hartman" authorityYear="1942" box="[1233,1365,1826,1852]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Psammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pendula">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC653FFA3BEBDF8F3B46BF8DF" box="[1233,1365,1826,1852]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. pendula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from sediments at a depth of 
<quantity id="4C9A9B3CC653FFA3BB9DF895B304F883" box="[497,570,1861,1888]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.52" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="m" value="352.0">352 m</quantity>
off 
<collectingCountry id="F3757649C653FFA3B80BF895B39BF8BC" box="[615,677,1861,1887]" name="Cuba" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cuba</collectingCountry>
using an anterior fragment with 85 segments and highlighting the “… large, pendulous organ on the third parapodium…”.Later, she (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C653FFA3B9B4F8B8B597F860" author="Hartman O." box="[984,1193,1896,1923]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref29666" refString="Hartman O. 1965. Deep-water Benthic Polychaetous Annelids off New England to Bermuda and Other North Atlantic Areas. Allan Hancock Foundation Publications, Occasional Paper 28." type="journal volume" year="1965">Hartman1965: 53</bibRefCitation>
)described 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC653FFA3BF4AF8B9B4A7F861" authorityName="Hartman" authorityYear="1965" box="[1318,1433,1896,1922]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Psammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="globula">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC653FFA3BF4AF8B9B4A7F861" box="[1318,1433,1896,1922]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P.globula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from off 
<collectingCountry id="F3757649C653FFA3BB25F85BB08BF846" box="[329,437,1931,1957]" name="Bermuda" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Bermuda</collectingCountry>
based on an anterior fragment with 54 segments, from sediments at a water depth of 
<quantity id="4C9A9B3CC653FFA3BA8FF87EB07EF82A" box="[227,320,1966,1993]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="m" value="1700.0">1700 m</quantity>
, and emphasized that the main difference between these two species was the presence of the “… globular process…” on the second parapodium, instead of being present on the third, as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC653FFA3BF76F802B4ADF808" authorityName="Hartman" authorityYear="1942" box="[1306,1427,2001,2027]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Psammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pendula">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC653FFA3BF76F802B4ADF808" box="[1306,1427,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. pendula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C653FFA3BA8FF824B0E3F7ED" author="Pettibone M. H." box="[227,477,2036,2062]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 89" refId="ref30430" refString="Pettibone M. H. 1997. Revision of the sigalionid species (Polychaeta) referred to Psammolyce Kinberg, 1856, Pelogenia Schmarda, 1861, and belonging to the subfamily Pelogeniinae Chamberlin, 1919. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 581: 1 - 89. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.581" type="journal article" year="1997">Pettibone (1997: 23)</bibRefCitation>
revised the 
<typeStatus id="54D9887BC653FFA3B815F825B392F7EC" box="[633,684,2037,2063]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">type</typeStatus>
material of both species and did not find any morphological
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDD36D9C652FFA2BA8FFEFFB094FE6C" blockId="13.[227,1437,303,399]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">differences to keep them as two separated species. However, there are some slight differences between these two species, and the key below includes them as distinct, pending a comparative study to clarify their differences.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3786552C652FFA2BA8FFE66B2B3FE33" box="[227,909,437,464]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="multiple">
