<subSubSection id="C3786552C652FFA2BA8FFC8CB0A5FB95" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDD36D9C652FFA2BA8FFC8CB06BFC95" blockId="13.[227,341,860,886]" box="[227,341,860,886]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<heading id="D09581B5C652FFA2BA8FFC8CB06BFC95" bold="true" box="[227,341,860,886]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC652FFA2BA8FFC8CB06BFC95" bold="true" box="[227,341,860,886]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDD36D9C652FFA2BA8FFC5AB0A5FB95" blockId="13.[226,1437,906,1142]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
The junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC652FFA2B865FC5BB3AEFC47" baseAuthorityName="Hartman" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[521,656,906,932]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Psammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pendula">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC652FFA2B865FC5BB3AEFC47" box="[521,656,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. pendula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC652FFA2B8CFFC5AB561FC46" authority="Hartman, 1965" authorityName="Hartman" authorityYear="1965" box="[675,1119,906,933]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Psammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="globula">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC652FFA2B8CFFC5AB2A3FC47" box="[675,925,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Psammolyce globula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C652FFA2B9C4FC5BB561FC46" author="Hartman O." box="[936,1119,906,933]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refId="ref29666" refString="Hartman O. 1965. Deep-water Benthic Polychaetous Annelids off New England to Bermuda and Other North Atlantic Areas. Allan Hancock Foundation Publications, Occasional Paper 28." type="journal volume" year="1965">Hartman, 1965</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is clearly congeneric but both the original descriptions and illustrations point out differences to be considered. For example, 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC652FFA2BA8FFC01B056FC09" baseAuthorityName="Hartman" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[227,360,976,1002]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Psammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="pendula">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC652FFA2BA8FFC01B056FC09" box="[227,360,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. pendula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a drop-like neuropodial lobe on segment III that is inserted at the neuroacicular level without a stalk (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C652FFA2BBCFFC24B3A2FBEE" author="Hartman O." box="[419,668,1011,1038]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="89 - 104" refId="ref29558" refString="Hartman O. 1942 b. The polychaetous Annelida. In: Report on the Scientific results of the Atlantis expeditions to the West Indies under the Joint Auspices of the University of Havana and Harvard University. Memorias de la Sociedad Cubana de Historia Natural 16 (2): 89 - 104." type="journal article" year="1942">Hartman 1942b: 106</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 9 fig. 20; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C652FFA2B952FC23B51EFBED" author="Pettibone M. H." box="[830,1056,1011,1038]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 89" refId="ref30430" refString="Pettibone M. H. 1997. Revision of the sigalionid species (Polychaeta) referred to Psammolyce Kinberg, 1856, Pelogenia Schmarda, 1861, and belonging to the subfamily Pelogeniinae Chamberlin, 1919. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 581: 1 - 89. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.581" type="journal article" year="1997">Pettibone 1997: 24</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 15e), whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C624D5AC652FFA2BF49FC24B4A3FBEE" authorityName="Hartman" authorityYear="1965" box="[1317,1437,1011,1037]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sigalionidae" genus="Psammolyce" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="globula">
<emphasis id="B916EACBC652FFA2BF49FC24B4A3FBEE" box="[1317,1437,1011,1037]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. globula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this neuropodial lobe is balloon-like, inserted at the supracicular level with a long stalk (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF34B28C652FFA2BE86FBC7B02FFBB7" author="Hartman O." pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refId="ref29666" refString="Hartman O. 1965. Deep-water Benthic Polychaetous Annelids off New England to Bermuda and Other North Atlantic Areas. Allan Hancock Foundation Publications, Occasional Paper 28." type="journal volume" year="1965">Hartman 1965: 265</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 3 fig. a). The 
<typeStatus id="54D9887BC652FFA2BB8CFBEAB32DFBB7" box="[480,531,1082,1108]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
material of both species should be revised in order to clarify the morphology of both species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
